                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.1115/11–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-01T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 1, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 2—12:48 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>648. ReDeptel 411, October 28, 7 p. m. Recommend with Terry’s<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d1401fn83">Carroll M. Terry, First Secretary of the Embassy in the
                        Philippines.</note> approval that warning as worded in reference telegram be
                    issued now <pb facs="1366" n="1356" xml:id="pg_1356"/> with addition of data on
                    next 60 days’ steamship sailings. Consulate General desires take no other action
                    this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macdonald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
